descript.abstract:
REFER TO ACCOMPANING CALW22_MTADTA.TXT FILE FOR FULL METATDATA.
CALWATER provides a standard nested watershed delineation scheme using the State Water Resources Control Board numbering scheme. The hierarchy of watershed designations consists of six levels of increasing specificity: Hydrologic Region (HR), Hydrologic Unit (HU), Hydrologic Area (HA), Hydrologic Sub-Area (HSA), Super Planning Watershed (SPWS), and Planning Watershed (PWS). The primary purpose of Calwater is the assignment of a single, unique code to a specific watershed polygon. THIS DATASET HAS BEEN UPDATED BY MONTEREY PENINSULA WATER MANAGEMENT DISTRICT. SEE PROCESS SECTION
descript.purpose: With increasing emphasis on water quality, fish, sedimentation, and other water related issues, the Board of Forestry recognized the need for a standard watershed boundary framework. The CALWATER project and resulting watershed data provide the basis for discussion and analysis of watershed issues within a common context.
